title: Dream1_FirstLoaves
tags: dream mission1 doris first_loaves canonical
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Memory Dreams — the illustrated short-films at the end of each in-game day.
// Author: Sven Aleko (Memory Dream Director)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/05_DREAM1_AND_DREAM2.md
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_1.md § 17
//         Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_2.md § 22
//
// In Mission 1-2 we ship 2 dreams + 5 variants of Dream 2:
//   Dream 1 — The First Loaves (Doris, 1972 kitchen at first light, 60s)
//   Dream 2 — The Last Week (Margery's bedroom in winter, 5 variants):
//     • Variant A — Cleanse Perfect / Erase Perfect-or-Acceptable (canonical, 85s)
//     • Variant B — Cleanse Acceptable / Sloppy (80s)
//     • Variant C — Erase Crossed-Core / Cleanse Crossed-Core (90s)
//     • Variant D — Listen path (75s — UNIQUE; Gerrold is the cast figure,
//                                 not Margery; ends on the player being thanked)
//     • Variant E — Defer (30s — the most restrained dream)
//
// These Yarn nodes carry the narrative TITLE OVERLAY + SUBTITLE that
// appears on the Bamao parchment frame during each dream. The actual
// scene animation + composer cues are driven by MemoryDreamSequencer.cs
// (Mission asmdef) consuming the same node names.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DreamTitle: The First Loaves
DreamSubtitle: — 1972

// ── 60-second beat sheet (titles only — full animation in Sequencer) ──
//  0:00–0:03  Fade in from black. Title card lower-third.
//  0:03–0:10  Wide kitchen establishing shot. Empty. No music yet.
//  0:10–0:15  Young Doris (24) fades in at the oven. Back to camera.
//  0:15–0:25  Pulls loaves out. Camera medium-close on her hands.
//              Composer's Doris motif begins — solo cello.
//  0:25–0:35  Bread crust crackle foley. VoluSmokeFX steam wisps rise.
//              Flour dust visible in the sun shaft.
//  0:35–0:50  Doris wipes hands on apron. She does not yet smile.
//              Looks at the door. Door does not open.
//  0:50–0:55  Stands still. Watches the door. Alone.
//  0:55–0:60  A subtle slow smile begins. Camera pulls back to wide.
//              Subtitle "— 1972" appears lower-third.
//              Composer's motif resolves on a held, unresolved-but-warm sustain.
//  0:60       Fade to amber.

===

title: Dream2_VariantA_CleansePerfect
tags: dream mission2 gerrold margery variant_a canonical
---
DreamTitle: The Last Week
DreamSubtitle: — Saltlight, last winter

// ── 85-second beat sheet ─────────────────────────────────────────
//  0:00–0:05  Fade in. Margery's bedroom in winter. Folded handkerchief
//              on bedside table. Soft amber lamp light.
//  0:05–0:10  Margery fades in, sitting up in bed. Soft-focused.
//              Her face is CLEARLY visible.
//  0:10–0:25  She picks up the handkerchief.
//  0:25–0:40  Looks at the embroidered "M" in the corner.
//              Camera extreme-close on the embroidery.
//  0:40–0:55  A small slow smile begins.
//  0:50–0:55  GERROLD appears briefly in the doorway — silhouette only.
//              He nods. He exits. (He was there for her. The dream
//              remembers it.)
//  0:55–0:70  She holds the handkerchief. Eyes closing softly.
//  0:70–0:80  At peace. The handkerchief is in her hand.
//  0:80–0:85  Camera pulls slowly back. Fade.
//
// Composer cue: M-MD02-A — Margery motif, solo violin → piano → cello,
//   full warm resolution. Major chord ending.

===

title: Dream2_VariantB_CleanseAcceptable
tags: dream mission2 gerrold margery variant_b
---
DreamTitle: The Last Week
DreamSubtitle: — Saltlight, last winter

// ── 80-second beat sheet ─────────────────────────────────────────
// Same set-piece + blocking as Variant A. Differences:
//   • Lens: GRIEF + GRACE + a faint trace of SHAME
//   • Margery's face SOFTENED by lens-blur (visible but slightly less clear)
//   • Her smile is visible
//   • Composer cue: M-MD02-B — Margery motif, slightly hesitant.
//     Resolves but on a softer chord.

===

title: Dream2_VariantC_Damaged
tags: dream mission2 gerrold margery variant_c crossed_core
---
DreamTitle: The Last Week
DreamSubtitle: — Saltlight, last winter

// ── 90-second beat sheet ─────────────────────────────────────────
// The dream the cozy player will REMEMBER if they Crossed-Core'd.
// Used for: Erase path (any outcome) OR Cleanse Crossed-Core.
//
// Differences from Variant A:
//   • Lens: GRIEF (heavy) + GRACE (sparse)
//   • Margery's face is FOG-BLURRED — player sees her shape, the
//     handkerchief, the smile, but NOT the features clearly.
//   • Camera at the 40–55s extreme close is on the HANDKERCHIEF, not
//     on her face. The camera is choosing to protect the player from
//     her absence.
//   • Gerrold's doorway silhouette LINGERS longer, looking in. He
//     does NOT nod.
//   • Composer cue: M-MD02-C — same melody, but ending on an
//     unresolved minor seventh.

===

title: Dream2_VariantD_Listen
tags: dream mission2 gerrold listen variant_d unique
---
DreamTitle: The Last Week, Told
DreamSubtitle: — Sunday evening, this year

// ── 75-second beat sheet — THE UNIQUE DREAM ──────────────────────
// The most narratively different variant. Gerrold is the cast figure,
// not Margery. The cozy game's first moment of the player being
// directly THANKED. Per Mission 2 Guide § 22.4.
//
//  0:00–0:10  The cottage chair. Gerrold's chair, alone, in the empty
//              bedroom. The bed is mostly off-frame. Margery is NEVER
//              visible.
//  0:10–0:30  Gerrold appears, sitting in his chair. Hands in lap.
//  0:30–0:50  Tight on his hands. Then his face. He is recounting —
//              to no one — what he just told you.
//  0:50–0:65  He looks DIRECTLY at the camera — at the player, who is
//              dreaming him. His eyes close softly, briefly. Open again.
//  0:65–0:71  One small smile.
//  0:71–0:75  Held for 4 seconds. Cut to black.
//
// Lens: GRIEF (gentle) + GRACE (full) + WONDER (a soft golden trace —
//        unique to this variant; the wonder of being heard).
// Composer cue: M-MD02-D — solo cello, no other instruments. The most
//   spare cue in the entire vertical slice.

===

title: Dream2_VariantE_Defer
tags: dream mission2 defer variant_e restrained
---
DreamTitle: An Empty Chair
DreamSubtitle:

// ── 30-second beat sheet — THE LIGHTEST DREAM ────────────────────
// The dream of "not knowing yet." Per Mission 2 Guide § 22.5.
//
//  0:00–0:06  The cottage. Margery's chair, empty. The book on its arm.
//              The cold cup of tea. The bed is empty. NOTHING ELSE.
//  0:06–0:30  Held shot. Silence after the first 6 seconds (only the
//              wind outside).
//
// Lens: GRACE only.
// Composer cue: A single sustained note for the first 6 seconds, then
//   silence. The most restrained moment in M1-2.

===

title: SleepTransition_M1_M2_Shared
tags: dream transition sleep shared
---
// ── 2.5-second Sleep Transition ──────────────────────────────────
// Plays at the end of every in-game day, just before each Memory Dream.
// Per Mission 1 Guide § 12.2 + § 17 + Mission 2 Guide § 22.
//
//  0.0s   Ledger book gently closes audibly (cloth-on-paper).
//  0.2s   Shop's audio softens to ~30%.
//  0.5s   Camera tilts upward toward the Hollow's ceiling, finding a
//          single beam of moonlight.
//  0.9s   Pickle stretches and curls (visible).
//  1.2s   Screen begins fading to warm amber.
//  1.8s   Audio fully silent.
//  2.5s   Amber fade completes; dream's first frame appears.

===

title: WakeTransition_M1_M2_Shared
tags: dream transition wake shared
---
// ── 3-second Wake Transition ─────────────────────────────────────
// Plays at the end of every Memory Dream. Per Mission 1 Guide § 17.4
// + Mission 2 Guide § 22.6.
//
//  0.0s   Dream's final frame holds.
//  0.5s   Screen fades to bright morning gold.
//  1.4s   A single bird outside the Hollow's window.
//  1.8s   Pickle's stretch + tail-flick.
//  2.2s   The day's morning cue enters softly. Varies by Dream 2 variant:
//           • Variant A: Doris's motif at low volume — normal cozy morning
//           • Variant B: Doris's motif slightly muted
//           • Variant C: Doris's motif at very low volume; a long held note
//           • Variant D: A piano motif — the Sunday-tea theme (M3+ teaser)
//           • Variant E: Silence; only the bird outside
//  3.0s   The Hollow interior renders fully. Player has control.

===

title: Mission02_Outro_Cinematic
tags: dream cinematic mission2_outro shared
---
DreamTitle: Day 2 ended.
DreamSubtitle: Tomorrow, the village will know.

// ── 30-second outro Cinematic ────────────────────────────────────
// Plays after Memory Dream 2 wakes. Per Mission 2 Guide § 23.
// Identical length across paths. Visual content differs.
//
//  0:00–0:08  Slow pan through the Hollow. Chairs sit empty. Pickle
//              sleeps on the windowsill. Fire in the stove is low.
//  0:08–0:18  Camera finds the workbench.
//              IF handkerchief returned: workbench is empty.
//              IF handkerchief still held: it is folded on the bench
//                                            beside the orb cradle.
//  0:18–0:25  Camera finds the shelves. DOR-001 softly glows.
//              Path A (Erase):   GER-007 clouded, partial.
//              Path B (Cleanse): GER-007 cleansed, full clarity.
//              Path C (Listen):  GER-007 NOT on the shelf — it is in
//                                Gerrold's cottage. The shelf has an
//                                empty space.
//              Path D (Defer):   GER-007 in its cloth on the counter,
//                                untouched.
//  0:25–0:30  Camera pulls back. Title overlay. Fade to black.
//
// Composer cue: Hearthbound main theme, final 20 seconds (full statement).

===
